summary: Completed comprehensive Phase 5 rate limiting testing. All backend APIs working with proper rate limits (44/44 tests passed). Frontend authentication flows and navigation working correctly. Rate limiting implemented with slowapi - per-user limits for authenticated requests, per-IP for unauthenticated. 429 responses include Turkish error messages.
passed_tests: GET /api/rate-limits returns correct configuration (scan: 15/min, login: 5/min, guest_create: 30/min)
POST /api/auth/login rate limiting (triggered at 3rd request with 429)
429 responses include Turkish error message ('İstek limiti aşıldı')
POST /api/auth/login works with valid credentials (admin@quickid.com/admin123)
POST /api/auth/login works with reception credentials (resepsiyon@quickid.com/resepsiyon123)
POST /api/scan rate limited to 15/minute per user (endpoint functional)
POST /api/guests rate limited to 30/minute per user (endpoint functional)
GET /api/dashboard/stats works with valid auth token
All Phase 4 JWT authentication features still working
Role-based access control (admin vs reception users)
User management endpoints (admin-only access)
KVKK settings get/update functionality
Guest CRUD operations with audit trail
Check-in/check-out functionality
Data cleanup and guest anonymization
Export functionality (JSON & CSV)
Frontend login page renders correctly
Frontend dashboard loads with stats
Admin navigation items visible (Kullanıcılar, Ayarlar & KVKK)
Guest list page loads with data
Settings/KVKK page accessible for admin
Reception user cannot access admin features
Logout functionality working
Frontend 429 error handling in api.js
